title: Sources
text: The data was taken from a dataset published by the Reef Life Survey. Because this map only requires certain columns, columns that included data such as the fish species were removed.

title: Interactive Map of Reef Life
text: Ever wondered what goes on in the bustling world of coral reefs? I’ve been exploring this through a project focused on reef life, using a dataset from the Reef Life Survey. Today, I’ve used this data and created an interactive map that lets you explore these underwater communities based on species counts, and another part that highlights the top 10 most common species and where they’re found. I have found that there is major reef life around places such as Australia, and that wrasses are very common in coral reefs.

title: About
text:
This project was created by Sophia Yao with the help of Alex Yao and ChatGPT. Here is Sophia’s Github account page and her email is sophia.jiani.yao@gmail.com.
The project uses data from Reef Life Survey about marine life in reefs.
This project was created as a part of Kane’s Data Science Bootcamp.
